Pakistan’s Banks, Government Offices, Markets Closed Dec. 5-6

-- B y   F a r h a n   S h a r i f
-- 
2011-12-01T10:03:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/pakistan-s-banks-government-offices-markets-closed-dec-5-6.html
Pakistan ’s stock exchanges, banks,
central bank, and businesses will be closed on Dec. 5 and Dec. 6
for the religious festival of Ashura, the ninth and 10th days of
Muharram, the first month of the Muslim calendar.  They will reopen on Dec. 7, according to notices issued by
the  Karachi Stock Exchange  and the  central bank .  Ashura marks the anniversary of the death 14 centuries ago
of Imam Hussein, Prophet Muhammad’s grandson.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Farhan Sharif in Karachi at 
